adcast of a sporting event interferes with the program's usual scheduling. ''Topik Petang'' last aired on October 16, 2013.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.an.tv/berita an.tv]\n\n[[Category:2000s Indonesian television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Indonesian television series]]\n[[Category:2006 Indonesian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2013 Indonesian television series endings]]\n[[Category:Indonesian television news programmes]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-tv-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up, addedorphantag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topik_Petang_(TV_program)"}
{"title_page": "Baranwal", "text_new": "{{short description|A Hindu community in India}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n| group           = Baranwal\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| regions         = India\n| langs           = [[Hindi]], [[Bhojpuri]]\n| rels            = [[File:Om symbol.svg|14px]] [[Hinduism]]\n}}\n'''Baranwal''' (also spelled '''Barnwal''', '''Burnwal''', '''Bernwal''', '''Varanwal''', '''Varnwal''', '''Barnawal''') is a [[Hindu]] community found throughout northern [[India]], including [[Bihar]], [[Jharkhand]], [[West Bengal]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[Gujarat]] along with a sprinkled presence in [[Rajasthan]], [[Haryana]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref name=\"PoI_UP\"/><ref>{{cite book |author=C. Dwarakanath Gupta |title=Socio-cultural History of an Indian Caste |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OJlpWwZkRDAC&pg=PA16 |year=1999 |publisher=Mittal |isbn=978-81-7099-726-9 |page=16 }}</ref> The name of the caste derives from \"Baran\" or \"Barn\", a former name of the [[Bulandshahr]] city.<ref name=\"PoI_UP\"/><ref>{{cite book |author=Kumar Suresh Singh |title=Communities, Segments, Synonyms, Surnames and Titles |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bfAMAQAAMAAJ |year=1996 |publisher=Anthropological Survey of India |isbn=978-0-19-563357-3 |page=113, 203}}</ref><ref name=\"PoI_UP\">{{cite book |title=People of India: Uttar Pradesh |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LxdWAAAAYAAJ |year=2005 |publisher=Anthropological Survey of India |isbn=978-81-7304-114-3 |page=200 }}</ref><ref>Smith, V. (1897). Art. XXIX.\u2014The Conquests of Samudra Gupta. Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society, 29(4), 859-910. doi:10.1017/S0035869X0002503X</ref>\n\n==Gotras==\nHistorically, there has been no unanimity regarding number and names of gotras, and there are regional differences between the list of gotras. There is 36 gotra in baranwal community. Some of the gotras like Kasyap and Kaushik are specific to Rajputs.{{sfn|People of India: Uttar Pradesh|2005|p=200}}\n{{Columns-list|#Garg\n#Vatsil\n#Goyal\n#Gohil\n#Karav\n#Deval\n#Kashyap\n#Vats\n#Atri\n#Vamdev\n#Kapil\n#Gaalab\n#Sinhal\n#Aarnay\n#Kashil\n#Upmanyu\n#Yamini\n#Parashar\n#Kaushik\n#Munas\n#Katyapan\n#Kondilya\n#Pulish\n#Bhrigu\n#Sarve\n#Angira\n#Krishrabhi\n#Udhwalak\n#Ashwalayan\n#Bharadwaj\n#Kankhal\n#Mudgal\n#Yamadgiri\n#Chyawan\n#Vedpramiti\n#Sanskritayan}}\n\n== References ==\n'''Notes'''\n{{notelist}}\n'''Citations'''\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:Social groups of Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Bania communities]]\n[[Category:Hindu surnames]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|A Hindu community in India}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n| group           = Baranwal\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| regions         = India\n| langs           = [[Hindi]], [[Bhojpuri]]\n| rels            = [[Hinduism]]\n}}\n'''Baranwal''' (also spelled '''Barnwal''', '''Burnwal''', '''Bernwal''', '''Varanwal''', '''Varnwal''', '''Barnawal''') is a [[Hindu]] community found throughout northern [[India]], including [[Bihar]], [[Jharkhand]], [[West Bengal]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[Gujarat]] along with a sprinkled presence in [[Rajasthan]], [[Haryana]], [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref name=\"PoI_UP\"/><ref>{{cite book |author=C. Dwarakanath Gupta |title=Socio-cultural History of an Indian Caste |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OJlpWwZkRDAC&pg=PA16 |year=1999 |publisher=Mittal |isbn=978-81-7099-726-9 |page=16 }}</ref> The name of the caste derives from \"Baran\" or \"Barn\", a former name of the [[Bulandshahr]] city.<ref name=\"PoI_UP\"/><ref>{{cite book |author=Kumar Suresh Singh |title=Communities, Segments, Synonyms, Surnames and Titles |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bfAMAQAAMAAJ |year=1996 |publisher=Anthropological Survey of India |isbn=978-0-19-563357-3 |page=113, 203}}</ref><ref name=\"PoI_UP\">{{cite book |title=People of India: Uttar Pradesh |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LxdWAAAAYAAJ |year=2005 |publisher=Anthropological Survey of India |isbn=978-81-7304-114-3 |page=200 }}</ref><ref>Smith, V. (1897). Art. XXIX.\u2014The Conquests of Samudra Gupta. Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society, 29(4), 859-910. doi:10.1017/S0035869X0002503X</ref>\n\n==Gotras==\nHistorically, there has been no unanimity regarding number and names of gotras, and there are regional differences between the list of gotras. There is 36 gotra in baranwal community. Some of the gotras like Kasyap and Kaushik are specific to Rajputs.{{sfn|People of India: Uttar Pradesh|2005|p=200}}\n{{Columns-list|#Garg\n#Vatsil\n#Goyal\n#Gohil\n#Karav\n#Deval\n#Kashyap\n#Vats\n#Atri\n#Vamdev\n#Kapil\n#Gaalab\n#Sinhal\n#Aarnay\n#Kashil\n#Upmanyu\n#Yamini\n#Parashar\n#Kaushik\n#Munas\n#Katyapan\n#Kondilya\n#Pulish\n#Bhrigu\n#Sarve\n#Angira\n#Krishrabhi\n#Udhwalak\n#Ashwalayan\n#Bharadwaj\n#Kankhal\n#Mudgal\n#Yamadgiri\n#Chyawan\n#Vedpramiti\n#Sanskritayan}}\n\n== References ==\n'''Notes'''\n{{notelist}}\n'''Citations'''\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:Social groups of Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Bania communities]]\n[[Category:Hindu surnames]]\n", "name_user": "Bluee Bell", "label": "safe", "comment": "added image", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baranwal"}
